@startuml
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Context.puml

Person(apiUser, "API Client / User", "Web or mobile client, or external API consumer")
System(apiGateway, "API Gateway", "Single external entry point; routing, auth, rate-limiting")
System(soccer, "Soccer Management System", "Microservices-based system for managing matches, leagues, teams and stadiums")

System_Ext(fd_org, "football-data.org", "External football data API (league, team, and match data)")
System_Ext(api_football, "API-Football", "External football data API (stadium/venue data)")

Rel(apiUser, apiGateway, "Sends requests (only entry point)", "HTTPS/REST")
Rel(apiGateway, soccer, "Forwards requests to appropriate microservices", "HTTPS/REST")
Rel(soccer, fd_org, "Imports league, team, and match data from", "REST/HTTP")
Rel(soccer, api_football, "Imports stadium/venue data from", "REST/HTTP")

note right of apiGateway
API Gateway is the single external entry point for all clients.
Performs routing, authentication, rate limiting and request validation.
end note

note right of soccer
System constraints:
- Match Service is the core orchestrator/data aggregator
- Each service owns its own PostgreSQL database
- Local testing uses H2
- Docker Compose uses PostgreSQL
- Deployment uses 9 Docker containers
  (5 service containers + 4 PostgreSQL containers)
end note

@enduml